"{\"uid\": \"cityam.com-theres-nothing-like-the-olympics-paris-2024-will-prove-that-again\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Featured  Submit a story  Tell us your story.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 45, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Featured  Submit a story  Tell us your story.\", \"from\": 47, \"to\": 92, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Featured  Submit a story  Tell us your story.\", \"from\": 94, \"to\": 139, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"By:Matt Hardy  Deputy Sports Editor - City AM  The Olympics is a bastion of patriotism and memories of a childhood well spent; despite growing up and coming to terms with thepoliticisationof it, says Deputy Sports Editor Matt Hardy.\", \"from\": 141, \"to\": 373, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 362, \"end\": 372, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Hardy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Matt Hardy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13474373\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Hardy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Hardy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Being asked about early sporting memories often leaves a sense of complete and utter embarrassment.\", \"from\": 375, \"to\": 474, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Now 24, I do not vividly remember the 2003 Rugby World Cup or the then \\\"clean\\\" dominance of Lance Armstrong on the Tour de France.\", \"from\": 476, \"to\": 606, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 568, \"end\": 583, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lance_Armstrong\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8183656053372133e-41, \"text\": \"Lance Armstrong\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lance_Armstrong\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lance_Armstrong\"}, {\"begin\": 591, \"end\": 605, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"score\": 0.9992657264372027, \"rank\": 0.0007329625857995612, \"text\": \"Tour de France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"My first rugby memory is one of tears - returning home from Twickenham after my Premiership side were spanked at HQ - while England not qualifying for the Euros 16 years ago and the 2005 Ashes are just about in the memory bank.\", \"from\": 608, \"to\": 835, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 668, \"end\": 678, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twickenham_Stadium\", \"score\": 0.9999945270728557, \"rank\": 5.472957323098845e-06, \"text\": \"Twickenham\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twickenham_Stadium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twickenham_Stadium\"}, {\"begin\": 732, \"end\": 739, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/England_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.8369874848484264, \"rank\": 0.15229154185573815, \"text\": \"England\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/England_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/England_national_rugby_union_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But in 2008, at the age of eight, my love for sport changed.\", \"from\": 837, \"to\": 897, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Stay in the game with The Turnover: your weekly roundup of sport business news, expert analysis and behind\\u2011the\\u2011scenes stories from City\\u202fAM's sports desk.\", \"from\": 899, \"to\": 1052, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Because early in the morning I'd wake up, run downstairs, and watch sport until mid-afternoon.\", \"from\": 1054, \"to\": 1148, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Every day for two weeks that was my life.\", \"from\": 1149, \"to\": 1190, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And what was this paradise of sporting action, where athletics was followed by badminton, canoeing and gymnastics?\", \"from\": 1192, \"to\": 1306, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 1307, \"to\": 1325, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The quadrennial event really is a highlight of a sporting cycle, up there with the Fifa World Cup and rugby's equivalent.\", \"from\": 1327, \"to\": 1448, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1415, \"end\": 1424, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIFA_World_Cup\", \"score\": 0.997687076914355, \"rank\": 0.002134560998053767, \"text\": \"World Cup\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIFA_World_Cup\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIFA_World_Cup\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was a display of patriotism, where you'd support anyone and everyone as long as they had the words \\\"Team GB\\\" or \\\"Great Britain\\\" slapped across their kit.\", \"from\": 1450, \"to\": 1606, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The splendour of the opening ceremony in all of its regimented glory and the emotion I'd never thought I'd see from archers, triathletes and weightlifters.\", \"from\": 1608, \"to\": 1763, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was a sporting awakening.\", \"from\": 1765, \"to\": 1793, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And since then - in the three Olympiads that have followed in London, Rio de Janeiro and Tokyo - the Olympic Games have continued to captivate my attention.\", \"from\": 1795, \"to\": 1951, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1857, \"end\": 1863, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999999984252099, \"rank\": 1.558584656751588e-09, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 1865, \"end\": 1879, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.47353659356717e-18, \"text\": \"Rio de Janeiro\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\"}, {\"begin\": 1884, \"end\": 1889, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999990363744569, \"rank\": 9.635705145925736e-07, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So on Friday of this week, when the opening ceremony down the River Seine gets underway in Paris, again I will be drawn to the splendour and gravitas of this fortnight of dreams.\", \"from\": 1953, \"to\": 2131, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2015, \"end\": 2026, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 2044, \"end\": 2049, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999998262865, \"rank\": 1.7350628249651688e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Growing up since Beijing the politics, drama and grossness that comes with these types of events has shown itself.\", \"from\": 2133, \"to\": 2247, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2150, \"end\": 2157, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.999999976740128, \"rank\": 2.3259671684548492e-08, \"text\": \"Beijing\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We have seen doping scandals, athletes denied access to the Games because of their biology and problems with poor attendances.\", \"from\": 2248, \"to\": 2374, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But back in Europe for the first time since London - really one of the greatest ever Games - the Olympics will shine for a British audience once again.\", \"from\": 2376, \"to\": 2527, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2420, \"end\": 2426, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999999984252099, \"rank\": 1.558584656751588e-09, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 2499, \"end\": 2506, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.8470732693969634, \"rank\": 0.1804010517143402, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Team GB won 51 medals in Beijing.\", \"from\": 2529, \"to\": 2562, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2529, \"end\": 2536, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999999999577085, \"rank\": 2.4530171813908574e-11, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 2554, \"end\": 2561, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.999999976740128, \"rank\": 2.3259671684548492e-08, \"text\": \"Beijing\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I probably watched them all at some point that summer.\", \"from\": 2563, \"to\": 2617, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In London it was 65, Rio saw a return of 67 and in Tokyo it was 64.\", \"from\": 2618, \"to\": 2685, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2621, \"end\": 2627, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999999984252099, \"rank\": 1.558584656751588e-09, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 2639, \"end\": 2642, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999942265276, \"rank\": 5.77357393036569e-09, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2669, \"end\": 2674, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999990363744569, \"rank\": 9.635705145925736e-07, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Our stock has risen and expectations are higher now than 16 years ago.\", \"from\": 2687, \"to\": 2757, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But in a world where there is sport on every single day the Olympics, for me, remains the one.\", \"from\": 2759, \"to\": 2853, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is the singular event where I cancel plans to watch the shooting, delay a dinner to see the 5,000m, and ignore my family until the open water swimming has concluded.\", \"from\": 2854, \"to\": 3022, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympics, and our success in it, makes me proud to be British; and it makes me wonder just how there are people who do not like any sport at all.\", \"from\": 3024, \"to\": 3173, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"My Olympic memories have been good ones; Chris Hoy, Super Saturday, the Brownlee Brothers and Bethany Shriever.\", \"from\": 3175, \"to\": 3286, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3247, \"end\": 3255, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Justin_Brownlee\", \"score\": 0.9986061752430788, \"rank\": 0.001394395849217471, \"text\": \"Brownlee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Justin_Brownlee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Justin_Brownlee\"}, {\"begin\": 3256, \"end\": 3264, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brother\", \"score\": 0.9999998944258606, \"rank\": 9.932593607207109e-08, \"text\": \"Brothers\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brother\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brother\"}, {\"begin\": 3269, \"end\": 3285, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beth_Shriever\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bethany Shriever\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beth_Shriever\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beth_Shriever\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That's probably why it's an event of joy in my psyche.\", \"from\": 3287, \"to\": 3341, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But even if that was not the case I'd be tuning in every day from this Friday.\", \"from\": 3343, \"to\": 3421, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I cannot wait to get lost in rugby sevens, skateboarding and climbing.\", \"from\": 3423, \"to\": 3493, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I cannot wait to shout at the swimming relays, the surfing and race walk.\", \"from\": 3494, \"to\": 3567, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympic Games, in all of its politicised glory, remains the greatest show on Earth.\", \"from\": 3569, \"to\": 3656, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That is undeniable.\", \"from\": 3657, \"to\": 3676, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Share this article  Subscribe to the City AM newsletter to have our top stories delivered directly to your inbox.\", \"from\": 3678, \"to\": 3791, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow us for breaking news and latest updates\", \"from\": 3793, \"to\": 3839, \"entities\": []}]}"